  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation where your best friend is dating your crush can be emotionally challenging, but it\u2019s important to handle it with maturity, honesty, and respect for everyone involved. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - Give yourself time to process your emotions. It\u2019s okay to feel hurt, disappointed, or even jealous. Suppressing your feelings may make it harder to move forward.\n\n### 2. **Communicate (If Appropriate)**\n   - If you\u2019ve made your feelings about your crush known to your best friend, they may have acted without realizing the impact on you. If you feel comfortable, have an honest and calm conversation with your friend about how you\u2019re feeling. Avoid blaming or accusing them\u2014focus on expressing your emotions.\n\n### 3. **Respect Their Relationship**\n   - If your friend and your crush are happy together, try to respect their relationship. It\u2019s not fair to interfere or expect them to break up because of your feelings.\n\n### 4. **Take a Step Back**\n   - If the situation feels overwhelming, it\u2019s okay to take some space to focus on yourself. Spend time with other friends, pursue hobbies, or engage in self-care to help you heal.\n\n### 5. **Reframe Your Perspective**\n   - Try to see this as an opportunity for growth. Not all crushes turn into relationships, and sometimes things happen for a reason. Focus on the qualities you\u2019re looking for in a partner and remain open to meeting someone new.\n\n### 6. **Strengthen Your Friendship (If Possible)**\n   - If your friendship is important to you, try to work through this situation together. Over time, your feelings for your crush may fade, and your friendship could become stronger.\n\n### 7. **Seek Support**\n   - Talk to a trusted friend, family member, or therapist about how you\u2019re feeling. Sometimes an outside perspective can help you process the situation more clearly.\n\n### 8. **Let Go (If Necessary)**\n   - If your feelings for your crush or the situation with your friend are causing too much pain, it\u2019s okay to distance yourself for a while. Prioritize your mental and emotional well-being.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s natural to feel hurt in this situation, but with time and perspective, things will get better. Focus on healing and moving forward in a way that\u2019s healthy for you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
